'30:26': [
{sup:"a", word:"light", vrefs:"Isa. 60:19-20"},
{sup:1, word:"sevenfold", lines:["In the consideration of the godly people, mainly the prophets, there was the expectation that the Messiah would come to restore not only the kingdom of Israel (cf. {Act1:6|Acts 1:6}) but also the entire universe, especially the sun, the moon, and the stars, for the growing of the living things on the earth, that the earth might be very rich in produce. In the restoration the light of the sun will be sevenfold not for scorching but for shining, for giving sunshine to grow the living things on earth. This means that the heavens will answer the earth and cause it to grow things in a rich way ({Hos2:21|Hosea 2:21}-{Hos2:22|22}). The sun&rsquo;s shining seven times brighter indicates that the produce of the earth will be seven times richer than it is in this age. At that time there will be no scarcity but rather plenitude. See notes {Hos6:11^1|11<sup>1</sup>} in {Hos6|Hosea 6} and {Joe3:18^1|18<sup>1</sup>} in {Joe3|Joel 3}."]},
],
