'44:28': [
{sup:"a", word:"Cyrus", vrefs:"2&nbsp;Chron. 36:22-23; Ezra 1:1-2; 6:3; Isa. 45:1, 13"},
{sup:1, word:"shepherd", lines:["In chs. {Isa43|43}&mdash;{Isa45|45} Christ as the Servant of Jehovah is typified by Cyrus king of Persia, who was Jehovah&rsquo;s Shepherd and who fulfilled all the desires of Jehovah. Cyrus served God by defeating Babylon, God&rsquo;s enemy ({Isa48:14|48:14}), which had captured His people and destroyed the temple ({2Ki24|2&nbsp;Kings 24}&mdash;{2Ki25|25}), by declaring the release of Israel from captivity, and by issuing a decree allowing the Jews to rebuild their temple in Jerusalem ({Isa45:13|45:13}; {Ezr1:2|Ezra 1:2}-{Ezr1:3|3}). These three things are types, signifying Christ&rsquo;s defeating Satan ({Heb2:14|Heb. 2:14}), releasing His believers from Satan&rsquo;s captivity ({Luk4:18|Luke 4:18b}; {Eph4:8|Eph. 4:8}), and building up the church as God&rsquo;s temple ({Mat16:18|Matt. 16:18}; {Eph2:21|Eph. 2:21}). See {Isa41:2^1|note 2<sup>1</sup>} in {Isa41|ch. 41}."]},
],
